iv><div class="row"><b>DevOps &amp; Observability:</b>CI/CD Pipelines, Docker, Terraform, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps, Datadog (RUM, Tracing), CloudWatch, App Insights</div></div></section><section><h2 class="sectionTitle ">Professional Experience</h2><div class="list"><article class="entry break-avoid"><div class="entryHead"><div class="company">AdoptSequence &amp; AdoptIQ (Curtis Digital Inc.) — Remote</div><div class="meta"><span class="role">Solution Architect</span><span>Oct 2023 – May 2025</span></div></div><p class="summary">Led architecture and platform engineering for two SaaS products: an onboarding/automation platform and an A/V enhancement workflow service.</p><ul class="bulletList"><li>Led backend migration of AdoptSequence from AWS Lambda → Trigger.dev to support long-running video processing.</li><li>Architected end-to-end audio/video enhancement workflows using FFmpeg, Whisper, and AI voice synthesis.</li><li>Integrated Supabase for real-time sync and Postgres storage; replaced Ably, lowering latency and cost.</li><li>Operationalized RUM + APM in Datadog with CloudWatch signals; guided devs to review error patterns, improving iteration speed by ~50%.</li><li>Implemented PostHog-based interaction analytics with Kafka ingestion, ClickHouse OLAP, and Redis caching; authored the event schema and ETL, reducing time-to-activation and improving onboarding efficiency.</li><li>Owned the full DevOps lifecycle: CI/CD pipelines, infrastructure automation, deployment strategy, monitoring, and cloud cost optimization across AWS and Cloudflare.</li><li>Managed multi-repo codebases on GitHub with standardized PR reviews and automation.</li><li>Mentored junior developers, enforced best practices, and led roadmap execution with founders.</li><li>Integrated Clerk authentication across multiple applications.</li></ul><div class="techHeader">Tech Stack</div><div class="techGroup">TypeScript, JavaScript, Node.js, React, Remix, Lit, Astro, Next.js</div><div class="techGro