CD Pipelines, Docker, Terraform, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps, Datadog (RUM, Tracing), CloudWatch, App Insights</div></div></section><section><h2 class="sectionTitle ">Experience</h2><div class="list"><article class="entry break-avoid"><div class="entryHead"><div class="company">AdoptSequence &amp; AdoptIQ (Curtis Digital Inc.) — Remote</div><div class="meta"><span class="role">Solution Architect</span><span>Oct 2023 – May 2025</span></div></div><p class="summary">Led architecture and platform engineering for two SaaS products: an onboarding/automation platform and an A/V enhancement workflow service.</p><ul class="bulletList"><li>Managed multi-repo codebases on GitHub with standardized PR reviews and automation.</li><li>Mentored junior developers, enforced best practices, and led roadmap execution with founders.</li></ul></article><article class="entry break-avoid"><div class="entryHead"><div class="company">Colliers International (via TopCoder) — Remote</div><div class="meta"><span class="role">Senior Full-stack Developer</span><span>Oct 2021 – Sep 2023</span></div></div><p class="summary">Modernized internal apps for a global commercial real-estate firm, replacing third-party tools with Azure-native and AWS-native services.</p><ul class="bulletList"><li>Replaced a 3rd-party valuation tool with an internal AWS solution (EC2, S3, SES, RDS) in 3 weeks; cut vendor cost ~60–80% and absorbed additional developer cost solo.</li><li>Architected microservices on Azure Functions backed by Cosmos DB + SQL Server; reduced API p95 latency ~30–50%.</li><li>Implemented IaC + CI/CD with Terraform and Azure DevOps.</li><li>Mentored engineers and led POCs with architects/BAs; reduced new-hire ramp ~30–50% and accelerated concept-to-pilot ~2x.</li><li>Drove code reviews and onboarding standards; PR cycle time −20–35%, post-release defects −20–40%.</li></ul></article><article class="entry break-avoid"><div class="entryHead"><div class="company">Relisource Inc. — Dhaka, Bangladesh</div><div class="meta"><span class="role">Senior Software Engineer</span><span>Nov 2018 – Aug 2021</span></div></div><ul class="bulletList"><li>Developed a Clinical Trial Management System for a global pharmaceutical client.</li><li>Built an enterprise LMS platform with mobile support for educational clients.</li><li>Actively mentored team members on architecture and clean code practices.</li></ul></article><article class="entry break-avoid"><div class="entryHead"><div class="company">Astha IT — Dhaka, Bangladesh</div><div class="meta"><span class="role">Senior Software Engineer</span><span>Mar 2014 – Oct 2018</span></div></div><ul class="bulletList"><li>Led development for enterprise systems in logistics, education, and fintech.</li><li>Mentored junior engineers and participated in system architecture, client demos, and delivery cycles.</li></ul></article></div></section><section><h2 class="sectionTitle ">Education</h2><div class="entry"><div class="degree">Bachelor of Computer Science and Engineering</div><div class="line">Shahjalal University of Science and Technology · 2013</div></div></section></article>"`;

